text.tspan: You don't need the whole of both, but it might help keep it flat.
Cut the intricate inlets before removing much
of the paper, so you have something to hold onto!
It's also less brittle at that point.
Cut out where the studs/hips poke through.
(or a dome and two round plates)
Geometry note: Centering the arrows within halves or quadrants would be incorrect.
Instead, they should be translated by a half or quarter revolution relative to each other,
for correct spacing between the first and last arrow.
